  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "Add the chicken to the pot and cook until browned on all sides, about 5-7 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic, paprika, cumin, salt, and pepper to the pot and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Stir in the salsa, coconut cream, and lemon juice, and bring the mixture to a simmer.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and let the tagine simmer, covered, for 20-25 minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through.",
    "Taste and adjust the seasoning as needed.",
    "Serve the tagine hot, garnished with fresh parsley or cilantro, if desired.",
    "Let the tagine cool completely before refrigerating or freezing for later use."
